# Wiki skill (auto-trigger surface)

When the user says things like the phrases below, route to the **wiki skill** and persist to `wiki/`. Do NOT invent file paths — always go through the skill.

## Trigger phrases

- "မှတ်ထားစမ်း", "wiki ထဲ save လုပ်ပါ", "note ယူထား"
- "decision တစ်ခုယူထား", "ADR ရေးပါ"
- "remember this", "save to wiki", "remember this for next time"
- "convention သတ်မှတ်ထား", "naming rule remember လုပ်ထား"
- "snippet သိမ်းထား", "code လေး save ပါ"
- "reference attach လုပ်ပါ"
- "architecture diagram သိမ်းထားပါ"

## Dual-track (wiki vs session)

| Track | Path | Git | Role |
| ----- | ---- | --- | ---- |
| **Wiki** | `wiki/` | Committed | Skill entries — frontmatter, English slug, classify → folder |
| **Session** | `docs/sessions/` | Gitignored | Local detail after implementation — **not** a wiki skill save target |

- Wiki skill: **never** save skill entries into `docs/`.
- After implementation work, **both** tracks are mandatory — see always-on rule `06-documentation-hygiene.mdc` (user need not say "မှတ်ထား").

## Classification → folder mapping

| Intent | Folder | Filename |
|---|---|---|
| "Why we chose X" / trade-off | `wiki/decisions/` | `NNN-<slug>.md` |
| "We always do X like this" | `wiki/conventions/` | `<slug>.md` |
| Architecture / diagrams | `wiki/architecture/` | `<slug>.md` |
| Reusable code snippet | `wiki/snippets/` | `<slug>.md` (markdown only — code in fenced block) |
| Loose note / idea / TODO | `wiki/notes/` | `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` |
| External link / doc | `wiki/references/` | `<slug>.md` |

## Required frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: <title>
type: <decision|convention|architecture|snippet|note|reference>
date: YYYY-MM-DD
tags: [<tag>, <tag>]
---
```

## Rules

1. **Always** use absolute paths in Write tool calls.
2. **Always** include the frontmatter block.
3. **Never** save wiki skill entries into `src/`, `docs/` (outside wiki), or repo root.
4. Filename slug = lowercase kebab-case, English only.
5. **Never** use `.ts`/`.tsx` for snippets — markdown `.md` only (frontmatter breaks Prettier).
6. After writing, confirm to user with the file path.
